defaulte on future production.  Kier Group plc has established a Non-Vocational Qualification (NVQ) Centre at Greenburn. To date the Centre has completed 116 vocational qualifications in level 2 Plant Operations plus 6 supervisors achieving level 3 awards.
default&#xa0;
defaultCase Study 3: 
defaultSibelco Kingsteignton (Bovey Basin, Devon) Ball Clay Operations
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Devon Ball Clay operations provide a range of plastic clays unique in Europe and much of the rest of the world. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe properties of these premium Ball Clays and the consiste
defaultncy of the blended products are very highly regarded globally, with exports to over 80 countries and the fact that more than 50% of the world’s sanitary
default 
defaultware contains UK Ball Clay as an essential ingredient. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThere are few if any viable alternatives to the
default UK Ball Clay component in the UK and the EU sanitary ceramics industry. 
default&#xa0;
defaultSanitary
default 
defaultware producers regard the UK Ball Clays as essential to their production process. 
default&#xa0;
defaultSimilarly there are currently no viable substitute materials for Ball Clay in most other c
defaulteramic applications. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe UK Ball Clay is of great importance with potentially in the order of 70-80,000 jobs at risk if the supply of ball clay is interrupted. (Source: DTI). 
default&#xa0;
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultTypically ceramic manufacturers cannot carry large stocks of Ball Clay and th
defaultus are highly dependent on the producers for frequent and uninterrupted deliveries.
default 
defaultThe recently published National Planning Policy Framework reaffirmed the status of Ball Clay as a nationally important mineral in the context of the English planning syste
defaultm. 
default&#xa0;
default 
defaultThis status is nothing new and has been consistently afforded to Ball Clay in the UK since the Government’s Standing Conference in the 1940s, in part, due to its scarcity and limited distribution in the global context.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultSibelco’s operations 
defaultcontribute some £15m to the local economy of Newton Abbot and sustain direct employment of over 200 people in the local area, together with a significant number of indirect jobs from servicing through to catering. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe international trade in Ball Clay is a
defaultlso an integral element in sustaining Devon’s local ports, particularly Teignmouth, with between 80 and 90% of extracted mineral being exported. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe export of Ball Clay through Teignmouth consistently equates to circa 60% of the total annual tonnage throu
defaultgh the docks, being almost twice the volume of the next highest tonnage (animal feed). (Source: Teignmouth Harbour Commissioners Financial Report: Y/E April 2011).
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe £10m realignment of the B3193 Chudleigh Road currently being developed, will release 
defaultapproximately 3,500,000 tonnes (3.5mt) of consented premium grade plastic clays with an estimated 81% yield (average yield of Bovey Basin Ball Clays is circa 65%), over the next 22 years. 
default&#xa0;
defaultHowever, the 3.5mt is only the first phase of development, with the
default existing B3193 currently sterilising an estimated total of 24mt of premium grade Ball Clay.
